This paper is primarily focused on the optimization of communication in distributed deep learning, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of network infrastructure on communication, which relates to computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also touches on the overlap of computation and communication, which is a topic in distributed computing (cs.DC). The use of deep learning in the paper suggests that it could also fall under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses potential challenges and research directions, which could be related to systems and control (cs.SY).
